<p>I read <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3855187/is-it-a-bad-idea-to-use-printstacktrace-in-android-exceptions" title="here">here</a> that <code>e.printStackTrace()</code> should not be used to catch exceptions on android.</p>  <p>On another source I read that  I should use <code>Log.e()</code> instead of <code>e.printStackTrace()</code>:</p>  <pre><code>... catch (Exception e) {  Log.e(TAG, "Foo did not work", e); } </code></pre>  <p>Do I have to manually remove these calls in the release build? What is the best practice to trace exception logs in Android?</p>